A book, Energy Insight NIGERIA, will be presented tomorrow by Centre for Petroleum Information (CPI), to mark its two decades of existence. The book captures thoughts of 45 contributors in the industry. According to the editor and former General Manager of Finance at Nigeria LNG Limited and NNPC-NAPIMS Victor Eromosele, “over the last two decades, CPI has built a large repository of information from its knowledge-sharing activities.” 